My father grew up in an orphanage and spoke little of his life there. He was just a number, and would get in trouble when he went to the parking lot of the nursing home his mother was quarantined with TB in. He would throw stones at her window to get her attention, to let her know he loved her. This whole magical concept of caring for the less fortunate and desire to remind children they are still loved despite not having parents, resonates as the wonders of imagination are applied for lasting fun.
